[{'type': 'heading', 'text': 'From Prediction to PRO-Diction Models: Incorporating Patient-Reported Outcomes Into Predictive Analytics', 'level': 1}, {'type': 'paragraph', 'text': 'By Jane Doe | September 20, 2025'}, {'type': 'paragraph', 'text': 'Machine-learning risk models can only reflect the clinical data they are fed. Without patient-reported outcome measures, the algorithms miss symptom severity, quality-of-life trends, and the day-to-day function data that oncologists rely on when tailoring care.'}, {'type': 'paragraph', 'text': 'Electronic capture of validated questionnaires and integration with the electronic health record now enables real-time alerts. Programs like PRO-CTCAE and PROMIS provide structured inputs that help teams anticipate toxicities and intervene before symptoms escalate.'}, {'type': 'heading', 'text': 'Implementation Checklist', 'level': 2}, {'type': 'paragraph', 'text': 'Teams rolling out patient-reported outcome platforms highlighted several practical steps:'}, {'type': 'list', 'items': ['Start with a narrow cohort to confirm workflows and clinical champions.', 'Automate outreach reminders so surveys arrive when patients expect them.', 'Feed summaries back to clinicians inside their native EHR in-basket.'], 'ordered': False}, {'type': 'paragraph', 'text': 'Organizations also cautioned against assuming every instrument maps neatly to existing analytics pipelines. Harmonizing terminology across legacy risk models remains an active project.'}]